{
  "text": "Even neglecting the gap in yields with industrial capitalintensive agriculture, low-input agriculture requires far more labor to replace the lack of external inputs [CITATION_1] . This would imply a global agricultural system where the workforce will be totally devoted to food production with almost no room for the industrial and service sector, let alone the compression of free time available for leisure activities. We doubt that high-income and mid-high-income countries would willingly accept this.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "142039367"
  },
